focus on creating (responsive) WordPress themes when it comes to client work</li>\n<li>Take on more (of the above) client work</li>\n<li>Become a JavaScript expert (too broad or vague, I know)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Study goals</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Finish an internship assignment for a movie production company based in Bangkok</li>\n<li>Follow a minor in entrepeneurship</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Travel goals</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Travel, work,Â orientateÂ and enjoy life in Asia for at least a few months. (planned)</li>\n<li>Visit at least 1 more country in the second part of 2013</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Fitness goals</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Deadlift 2.5x BW. (2.1/2.5)</li>\n<li>Squat 2x BW (1.61 / 2)</li>\n<li>Overhead Press 1x BW (0.67 / 1)</li>\n<li><del>Bench Press 1x BW (1 / 1)</del></li>\n<li>12 consecutiveÂ body weightÂ pull-ups</li>\n<li>20 consecutiveÂ body weightÂ dips</li>\n<li>Drink less beer (have less hangovers)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That is all I can come up with at the moment. All of these goals seem pretty clear to me, are definitely attainable, inspire me and have a deadline. These are not new year resolutions, these are mere items on a to do list.</p>\n<p>Did you set your goals for 2013 already? Tell me about them in the comments cause sharing goals is important, remember?!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="http://dannyvankooten.com/802/goals-for-2013/">Goals for 2013</a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/dannyvankooten/~4/0ctlQGGXKSA" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:50:"http://dannyvankooten.com/802/goals-for-2013/feed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:1:"1";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:45:"http://dannyvankooten.com/802/goals-for-2013/";}s:7:"summary";s:399:"<p>Boy, does time fly. Anyway, happy new year for all of you! Hope you had a blast during New Year&#8217;s Eve and are now ready to take on 2013. I know I am. I follow variousÂ life-hackingÂ or so called &#8220;self improvement&#8221; blogs and read on a few of them about the importance of